cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

This paper is primarily focused on program specialization and optimization techniques for logic programming, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper specifically deals with higher-order logic programming, which is a subfield of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed technique, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with logic programming optimization, which is related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
